notes: On Wednesday in ward 4 Chipinge west, youth chairperson Tsvakeyi Muzhambi and two other MDC members were followed by ZANU PF thugs and CIO agents, armed with guns and sporting dark glasses. The group abandoned their car and ran for safety, but Muzhambi was cornered and assaulted severely.

actor1: ZANU-PF: Zimbabwe African National Union-Patriotic Front
notes: Assaults on MDC officials and supporters intensified in the Chipinge area of Manicaland on Wednesday and Thursday, as ZANU PF continued its campaign of violence linked to the Constitutional outreach program. Two MDC supporters sustained broken limbs.

assoc_actor_1: ZANU-PF: Zimbabwe African National Union-Patriotic Front
notes: In another incident ZANU PF militia, led by the district chairperson John Kanindiriri, are reported to be assaulting people who fail to attend forced meetings in Chendambuya in Headlands, Manicaland province.

assoc_actor_1: ZANU-PF: Zimbabwe African National Union-Patriotic Front
notes: On Tuesday night armed soldiers, led by Major Muti Musakwa, forcibly removed property and goods belonging to the MDC district treasurer for Zvimba West, James Jonga. The soldiers looted his supermarket at Murombedzi growth point in Zvimba, Mashonaland West province, demanding that he vacate the premises

actor1: ZANU-PF: Zimbabwe African National Union-Patriotic Front
assoc_actor_2: PTUZ: Progressive Teachers Union of Zimbabwe
notes: Unions have complained that teachers in the country are once again increasingly becoming the main targets of ZANU PF sponsored violence and intimidation. This week the Progressive Teachers Union of Zimbabwe (PTUZ) hit out at the Ministry of Education for what it termed its reluctance to speak out against the targeting of teachers during the constitutional outreach exercise.

actor1: ZANU-PF: Zimbabwe African National Union-Patriotic Front
notes: Reports from Hurungwe in Mashonaland West province, allege that Chief Chundu is travelling around the district with ZANU PF activists Peter Madamombe and Bilo Kaunde. They are said to be threatening to beat up anyone planning to oppose the discredited Kariba draft during the outreach meetings.

actor1: ZNLWVA: Zimbabwe National Liberation War Veterans Association
